-- South African Singer Mhlongo Dies After Losing Cancer Battle, Times Says
-- Paul Richardson
-- 2010-06-17T06:17:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/south-african-singer-mhlongo-dies-after-losing-cancer-battle-times-says.html

          
          
             South African singer Busi Mhlongo
died on June 15 at the age of 62 after battling breast cancer,
the Times reported, citing Neil Comfort, a friend.  
 South African President  Jacob Zuma  paid tribute to Mhlongo
as a person who “inspired the nation and let the world know of
South Africa’s quest for freedom,” the Johannesburg-based
newspaper quoted him as saying.  
 Mhlongo performed with artists including Hugh Masekela,
Salif Keita and Manu Dibango, the newspaper said.  
